      "content": "From an economic standpoint, unchecked immigration can depress wages for low-skilled native-born workers by increasing labor supply in certain sectors. Regarding national security, porous borders create undeniable vulnerabilities that can be exploited by transnational criminal organizations and terrorist elements. Finally, an influx of undocumented immigrants places significant, unbudgeted strain on local social infrastructure, including schools, healthcare, and emergency services, which taxpayers must ultimately fund. These tangible impacts demonstrate that strict enforcement is not just ideological, but a necessary fiscal and security imperative.",
